## New finding

### Cost TL;DR misstates the run summary format

**File:** `docs/integration.md:448`

The doc shows ONE format:
> `Total cost: $0.4231 (3 unknown-cost invocation(s))`

But `tools/run.ts:110-127` has THREE actual format branches plus a no-line case:
- `count === 0` → no line at all
- All unknown (`knownCount === 0`) → `Cost: N unknown-cost invocation(s) (provider did not report tokens)`
- All known (`unknown_count === 0`) → `Total cost: $X.YZYZ over N invocation(s)`
- Mixed → `Total cost: $X.YZYZ (N unknown-cost invocation(s))` (the one the doc shows)

This is a Phase 5.7 operator-facing honesty issue — operators reading the doc and then running an all-known-cost run see a different format than promised.

**Fix:** Replace the single example with the actual format set. Either show all three formats explicitly (recommended) or list them by case:

```
The pipeline emits zero, one, or many invocations per run. The summary line
varies based on what was metered:

- Zero invocations: line is omitted.
- All unknown-cost invocations: `Cost: 3 unknown-cost invocation(s) (provider did not report tokens)`.
- All known-cost invocations: `Total cost: $0.4231 over 5 invocation(s)`.
- Mixed: `Total cost: $0.4231 (3 unknown-cost invocation(s))`.
```

